-- Ireland Has ‘Huge Task’ on EU Fiscal Vote, Minister Tells Post
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-03-18T12:55:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/ireland-has-huge-task-on-eu-fiscal-vote-minister-tells-post.html
Ireland has a “huge task” ahead
of it to get a yes vote in a referendum on the European fiscal
compact, which still remains “winnable,” Minister of State for
Finance Brian Hayes told the  Sunday Business Post  newspaper.  “This is going to be a difficult challenge,” he told the
Dublin-based newspaper. “It’s going to require an enormous buy-
in from civic society groups who are in favor of advancing this
country. We’ve a huge task ahead.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
 cheatley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
